#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. Rule"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 17. Chaphassāyatanasutta → āyatanasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | āyatana (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Chaphassāyatanasutta"
msgstr "17. The Six Fields of Contact"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.113"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.17:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn4.17:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ "
"dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha was educating, encouraging, firing up, and "
"inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the six fields "
"of contact."

msgctxt "sn4.17:1.3"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā "
"dhammaṃ suṇanti."
msgstr ""
"And those mendicants were paying heed, paying attention, engaging "
"wholeheartedly, and lending an ear."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.252"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Māra thought:"

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.2"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sappahaṃseti."
msgstr ""
"“This ascetic Gotama is educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the "
"mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the six fields of contact."

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.3"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā "
"dhammaṃ suṇanti."
msgstr ""
"And those mendicants are paying heed, paying attention, engaging "
"wholeheartedly, and lending an ear."

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ vicakkhukammāyā”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I go and pull the wool over their eyes?”"

#. VAR: undrīyati → udrīyati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.17:2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato "
"avidūre mahantaṃ bhayabheravaṃ saddamakāsi, apissudaṃ pathavī maññe "
"undrīyati. Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and made a terrifyingly loud "
"noise close by him. It seemed as if the earth were shattering. Then one of "
"the mendicants said to another:"

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.6"
msgid "“bhikkhu bhikkhu, esā pathavī maññe undrīyatī”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicant, mendicant, it seems like the earth is shattering!”"

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When this was said, the Buddha said to that mendicant:"

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.8"
msgid "“nesā, bhikkhu, pathavī undrīyati."
msgstr "“Mendicant, that’s not the earth shattering."

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.9"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tumhākaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato”ti."
msgstr "That’s Māra the Wicked come to pull the wool over your eyes!”"

msgctxt "sn4.17:2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.1"
msgid "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā,"
msgstr "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.2"
msgid "phassā dhammā ca kevalā;"
msgstr "touches, and thoughts, the lot of them—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.3"
msgid "Etaṃ lokāmisaṃ ghoraṃ,"
msgstr "this is the dreadful bait"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:3.4"
msgid "ettha loko vimucchito."
msgstr "that the world’s stupefied by."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.1"
msgid "Etañca samatikkamma,"
msgstr "But a mindful disciple of the Buddha"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.2"
msgid "sato buddhassa sāvako;"
msgstr "has transcended all that."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.3"
msgid "Māradheyyaṃ atikkamma,"
msgstr "Having gone beyond Māra’s dominion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.17:4.4"
msgid "ādiccova virocatī”ti."
msgstr "they shine like the sun.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.17:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."
